The paper focuses on knowledge graph learning, which involves integrating domain-specific knowledge bases with machine learning and data mining models. This topic is closely related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also proposes a new convolutional neural network (CNN)-based model, which falls under the category of deep learning (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of entity descriptions, which involves natural language processing (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper applies the proposed methods to real-world biomedical data, which involves database systems (cs.DB).
